<ns0:entry xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:ns1="http://schemas.google.com/g/2005" xmlns:ns2="http://schemas.google.com/projecthosting/issues/2009" ns1:etag="W/&quot;DEINQH47eCl7ImA9WhRaE04.&quot;">
		<ns0:id>http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/1694</ns0:id><ns0:author>
			<ns0:name>jamesfen...@gmail.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105008541472586726939/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">In ppapi/c/dev, PPAPI has already provided font support, but these APIs does not provided enough information for third-party library like cairo/skia to draw text on graphic surface. Thus we must rely on PPAPI's text drawing API. but these APIs do not support drawing rotated text.

&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
PPAPI can draw non-rotated text currently, but not rotated ones.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
Many graphical applications need to support rotated text .

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
We can either add rotated text support in PPAPI directly, or
expose more font information so that third-party library like cairo/skia/pango can be used to draw rotated text.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
either PPAPI supports rotated text drawing or cairo/pango can be used to draw rotated text.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
NaCl's graphical application can be more useful.
